  "name": "Metamagic: Twinned Spell",
  "ownership": {
    "default": 0
  },
  "type": "feat",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you cast a spell that targets only one creature and doesn't have a range of self, you can spend a number of sorcery points equal to the spell's level to target a second creature in range with the same spell (1 sorcery point if the spell is a cantrip).</p><p>To be eligible, a spell must be incapable of targeting more than one creature at the spell's current level. For example, @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.41JIhpDyM9Anm7cs]{Magic Missile} and @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.7u2obDvuvtZBkTfq]{Scorching Ray} aren't eligible, but @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.ctW81uiX56xZR2c5]{Ray of Frost} is.</p>",
